esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert triggers when throttling occurs during AWS Bedrock AgentCore Gateway invocations.
//
// Gateway throttling indicates that requests are being rate-limited due to exceeding
// allowed TPS (transactions per second) or quota limits. This can impact agent
// performance and user experience.
//
// Common causes of throttling:
// - High request volume exceeding service quotas
// - Burst traffic patterns
// - Insufficient provisioned capacity
//
// The alert is grouped by cloud account, region, and resource to identify
// which gateways are being throttled.
//
// To reduce alert noise, increase the threshold (e.g., `total_throttles > 10`).
// Consider requesting a service quota increase if sustained throttling occurs.
// For more details, see: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock-agentcore/latest/devguide/observability-gateway-metrics.html

FROM metrics-aws_bedrock_agentcore.metrics-*
| WHERE aws.dimensions.Operation == "InvokeGateway"
| STATS total_throttles = sum(aws.bedrock_agentcore.metrics.Throttles.sum) BY cloud.account.id, cloud.region, aws.dimensions.Resource
| WHERE total_throttles > 0
